## Step 3 — Back on Render

1. Your new `loaniq-webhook` repo will now appear in the list (refresh if needed)
2. Click it to select it
3. Fill in the settings:
   - **Name:** `loaniq-webhook`
   - **Region:** any (pick closest to India — Singapore)
   - **Branch:** `main`
   - **Runtime:** `Node`
   - **Build Command:** `npm install`
   - **Start Command:** `node index.js`
   - **Instance Type:** Free
4. Click **"Deploy Web Service"**
5. Wait ~2 minutes → you'll get a URL like `https://loaniq-webhook.onrender.com`

